SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1092
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Chuck Winstead-Brown, 2026
Sevierville Chamber of Commerce Friend of the
Year.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting that the members of this General Assembly should
acknowledge and applaud those community leaders who are wholly devoted to enhancing the
quality of life for their fellow citizens and improving and enriching the place they all call home;
and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Chuck Winstead-Brown, who was recently
named the 2026 Friend of the Year by the Sevierville Chamber of Commerce in honor of his
active involvement with the Chamber; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Winstead-Brown is the Special Events Coordinator for Ripley's Sevier
County Attractions; he is consistently involved with Chamber events as well as a strong
supporter of the tourism industry, a great representative for his company, and a valuable
member of the community; and
WHEREAS, in addition to encouraging new businesses to become part of the Sevierville
Chamber of Commerce, he serves the events committee and is an important connector of ideas
and people; and
WHEREAS, Chuck Winstead-Brown epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are
characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud Mr. Winstead-Brown for his dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
SJR1092
017187
- 1 -

REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we congratulate Chuck Winstead-Brown on being
named the 2026 Sevierville Chamber of Commerce Friend of the Year and extend to him our
best wishes for continued success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
